            "id": "4a67a514baa746e59647e",
            "questionText": "During a sunny afternoon, a student observes various phenomena involving electromagnetic waves. All electromagnetic waves, including visible light, travel at approximately $!$3 \\times 10^8 \\text{ m/s}$!$ in air. Visible light is the electromagnetic radiation perceived by the human eye, with wavelengths typically measured in nanometers, approximately between $!$400 \\text{ nm}$!$ and $!$700 \\text{ nm}$!$. What is the numerical value of the difference between the highest frequency and the lowest frequency of visible light in air?",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "9c7e4e5b20964015af77a",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by recalling the fundamental relation between the speed $!$v$!$, frequency $!$f$!$, and wavelength $!$\\lambda$!$ of electromagnetic waves. Please choose the correct formula that relates these quantities.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "ac9e6112-e5e7-48ec-bb82-50fa7044d14a"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = f\\lambda$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$f = v\\lambda$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = \\lambda/f$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$f = v/\\lambda$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "f00c924a881a4fb68ad0c",
                    "stepText": "Next, convert the shortest wavelength of visible light from nanometers to meters. What is the numerical value, in meters, corresponding to $!$400 \\text{ nm}$!$?",
