            "questionText": "A telecommunications engineer is designing a new communication network that uses microwaves for high-speed internet. Microwaves are electromagnetic waves characterized by their centimeter wavelengths. For precise network calibration, the engineer needs to work with different units. If a particular microwave signal has a wavelength of $!$6 \\text{ cm}$!$, calculate the numerical value of this wavelength in micrometers $!$(\\mu\\text{m})$!$.",
